  "sn36.1:1.1": "Linked Discourses 36",
  "sn36.1:2.1": "1 With Verses",
  "sn36.1:3.1": "1 Samādhi",
  "sn36.1:4.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three feelings.",
  "sn36.1:4.2": "What three?",
  "sn36.1:4.3": "Pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling.",
  "sn36.1:4.4": "These are the three feelings.”",
  "sn36.1:5.1": "“With samādhi and situational awareness,",
  "sn36.1:5.2": "a mindful disciple of the Buddha",
  "sn36.1:5.3": "understands feelings,",
  "sn36.1:5.4": "the cause of feelings,",
  "sn36.1:6.1": "where they cease,",
  "sn36.1:6.2": "and the path that leads to their ending.",
  "sn36.1:6.3": "With the ending of feelings, a mendicant",
  "sn36.1:6.4": "is hungerless, extinguished.”"
}